searchKeys.keyword: Relaciones Geograficas de la Nueva España

dataIdInfo.idPurp: Point file displaying the location and relationships of the 16th century place names compliled in volume 10 of the 'Relaciones Geográficas de Nueva España' by René Acuña.
dataIdInfo.idCredit:
SOURCE: Acuña, René. 1988. Relaciones Geográficas del siglo XVI: Nueva Galicia. 1 edition. México: Universidad Autónoma de México, Imprenta Universitaria.
CREATORS: 'Digging Into Early Colonial Mexico: A large-scale computational analysis of 16th century historical sources'
[2020]
dataIdInfo.idAbs:
COORDINATE SYSTEM: GCS_WGS_1984 (decimal degrees)

COLUMNS:

-My_FID10: unique identifier per location.

-X: X coord.

-Y: Y coord.

-Placename: Place name according to Acuña.

-ModernName: Modern place name.

-Alt_name: Alternative place names according to Acuña.

-References: Bibliography.

-Confidence: Place name location degree of confidence.

1: Location is 100% accuarate according to the sources we are using to locate the toponyms (e.g. Atlas 1800, Atlas 2010, INEGI).

2: The location is estimated from historical information (e.g. Gerhard, Garcia Cubas, De la Garza, Moreno Toscano, Cline, RG).

-Notes: Additional information.

-Type: Type of place name (e.g. Mountain Range, River, Hill, pueblo, estancia, barrio, etc.).

-Type2: Type of place name, when there is more than one mentioned in the RGs (e.g. Mountain Range, River, Hill, pueblo, estancia, barrio, etc.).

-Type_URL: Type according to the Alexandria Digital Library Feature Type Thesaurus [https://www2.usgs.gov/science/about/thesaurus-full.php?thcode=3].

-FID_Relate: If the toponym is related to another place name, this field contains the unique identifier of the toponym with which it is related. Correspond to My_FID10.

-FID_Relat2: If the toponym is related to a second place name, this field contains the unique identifier of the second toponym with which it is related. Correspond to My_FID10.

-Relation: relationship that the place name shares with FID_Relate. This can be administrative-political dependency (depends on), or locational (near, within, contains).

-Start_Date: foundation date.

-End_Date: last date.

-Time_span: the time-span associated with the usa of the place names, linked to Wikipedia.

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.
